Yellow Freight System Incsaid it filed with the Interstate Commerce Commission a rateincrease of 2.9 pct in Rocky Mountain territory,    It said the increase would offset labor and other costincreases and not make a contribution to operating margins.    The company said it took the independent action of filingfor the rate increase following suspension by the commission ofa general rate increase published by the Rocky Mountain MotorTariff Bureau. It noted that at the same time the commissionallowed similar increases published by the other regional ratebureaus. Reuter&#3;